@startuml
title Viaverse Request Creation — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nCreate sheet\nRequest wizard\nDraft state" as Client
component "API Gateway / App BFF\nRequest API\nAI facade\nMedia facade" as BFF
component "RequestController" as Controller
component "Request Use Cases\nCreateDraft\nUpdateDraft\nPublishRequest" as UseCases
component "Request Policies\ncapability\nrequired fields\nprivacy" as Policies
component "RequestRepositoryPort\nCategoryPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
database "PostgreSQL\nservice_request\nrequest_media\noutbox_event" as DB
component "media-service\nUploadSession\nMediaAsset" as Media
component "AI Provider Adapter\ncategory suggestion\nbudget guidance" as AI
component "MapProvider\ngeocode\narea normalize" as Maps
queue "Kafka / Spring Cloud Stream\nServiceRequestPublished\nMatchingRequested" as Kafka
component "search/matching consumers\nOpenSearch projection\nWorker opportunity queue" as Search

Client --> BFF : REST
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> DB : JPA adapter
BFF --> AI : suggestions
BFF --> Media : upload session
UseCases --> Maps : normalize location
UseCases --> Kafka : outbox publish
Kafka --> Search : consume

note bottom
marketplace-service owns ServiceRequest source-of-truth.
AI, Media and Maps are adapters/integrations, not owners of the request.
end note
@enduml
